-- Dogan Holding Surges Most in One Month on Power Plant Deals
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-05-29T15:09:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-29/dogan-holding-surges-most-in-one-month-on-power-plant-purchases.html
Dogan Sirketler Grubu Holding AS (DOHOL) , a
Turkish group of companies with interests in media and energy,
surged the most in a month after saying it agreed to buy two
wind power plants from the Agaoglu Group.  The shares advanced 5.9 percent to 72 kurus at the close in
Istanbul, the biggest intraday gain since April 25.  Dogan will buy a 33 megawatt plant in southern Mersin
province and a 93 megawatt plant in western Balikesir province,
the company said in a statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange 
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
